Cloudflare + Domain Setup Notes

Back to README: ./README.md
Detailed documentation: ./docs/cloudflare.md

1) Domain and DNS onboarding

- Buy a domain from your registrar.
- Move nameservers to Cloudflare.
- Wait for DNS propagation.

2) Record setup

- Add A/AAAA record for required subdomain(s) to origin public IP.
- Use proxied/unproxied mode based on service exposure policy.

3) SSL/TLS policy

- Set SSL/TLS mode to Full (strict) once origin certificates are valid.
- Avoid insecure fallback modes in production.

4) Origin hardening

- Restrict direct origin exposure wherever possible.
- Keep admin services private over Tailscale unless intentionally published.

5) HTTPS at origin

- Install and renew certificates (Certbot or equivalent).
- Validate endpoint with curl and browser checks.

